@dev Determine whether all approvals and signatures are in place for `importPosition`.
 If `return[0]` is `false`, calling `vat.hope(proxy.address)` will set the MakerDAO approval.
 If `return[1]` is `false`, `importFromProxyWithSignature` must be called with a controller signature.
 If `return` is `(true, true)`, `importFromProxy` won't fail because of missing approvals or signatures.

importFromProxy(address,address,uint256,.details: Transfer debt and collateral from MakerDAO (this contract's CDP) to Yield (user's CDP) Needs controller.addDelegate(importProxy.address, { from: user });

params.debtAmount: Normalized dai debt to move from MakerDAO to Yield. ndai * rate = dai
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
params.user: The user to receive the debt and collateral in Yield
params.wethAmount: weth to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in Yield, and low enough to make sure that debt left in MakerDAO is also collateralized.

importPosition(address,address,uint256,u.details: Fork part of a user MakerDAO vault to ImportProxy, and call importProxy to transform it into a Yield vault This function can be called from a dsproxy that already has a `vat.hope` on the user's MakerDAO Vault

params.debtAmount: Normalized debt to move ndai * rate = dai
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: fyDai Pool to use for migration, determining maturity of the Yield Vault

importPositionCheck().details: Determine whether all approvals and signatures are in place for `importPosition`. If `return[0]` is `false`, calling `vat.hope(proxy.address)` will set the MakerDAO approval. If `return[1]` is `false`, `importFromProxyWithSignature` must be called with a controller signature. If `return` is `(true, true)`, `importFromProxy` won't fail because of missing approvals or signatures.

importPositionWithSignature(address,addr.details: Transfer debt and collateral from MakerDAO to Yield Needs vat.hope(importProxy.address, { from: user });

params.controllerSig: packed signature for delegation of ImportProxy (not dsproxy) in the controller. Ignored if '0x'.
params.debtAmount: dai debt to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Denominated in Dai (= art * rate)
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
params.wethAmount: weth to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in Yield, and low enough to make sure that debt left in MakerDAO is also collateralized.

importVault(address,address,uint256).details: Fork a user MakerDAO vault to ImportProxy, and call importProxy to transform it into a Yield vault This function can be called from a dsproxy that already has a `vat.hope` on the user's MakerDAO Vault

params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: fyDai Pool to use for migration, determining maturity of the Yield Vault

importVaultWithSignature(address,address.details: Transfer a whole Vault from MakerDAO to Yield Needs vat.hope(importProxy.address, { from: user });

params.controllerSig: packed signature for delegation of ImportProxy (not dsproxy) in the controller. Ignored if '0x'.
params.maxDaiPrice: Maximum fyDai price to pay for Dai
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
